<?xml version="1.0"?>
<rdf:RDF xmlns="http://w3id.org/opino/"
     xml:base="http://w3id.org/opino/"
     xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"
     xmlns:owl="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
     xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
     xmlns:xml="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"
     xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
     xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#">
    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/">
        <owl:versionIRI rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/0.1.0"/>
        <owl:imports rdf:resource="http://purl.org/emmedi/hico/2020-03-31"/>
        <dc:creator xml:lang="en">Andrea Schimmenti</dc:creator>
        <dc:date rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2026-04-30T14:30:00</dc:date>
        <dc:description xml:lang="en">OPINO (OPINion ONtology) is an ontology for the formal 
representation of opinions as Knowledge Graphs, grounded in 
the Description and Situation (DnS) Ontology Design Pattern (Gangemi and 
Mika 2003) and the DOLCE+DnS Ultralite foundational ontology (DUL). 

OPINO adopts DnS as its core architectural backbone. Its primary purpose 
is to serve as a domain-agnostic interface for representing opinions 
across heterogeneous contexts, without committing to a specific 
representational paradigm. In this context, an opinion is understood as 
a perspective-dependent description of an entity, premised on a construed 
state of affairs. Representations built with OPINO can be aligned to or 
converted into other models depending on the requirements of a given 
application. For instance, in the context of projects leveraging CRMinf 
as the primary model for representing propositional content, OPINO can 
work as a neutral interface layer that bridges the opinion&apos;s epistemic 
structure with CRMinf&apos;s inference and belief machinery. Similarly, OPINO 
representations can be mapped to Digital Hermeneutics or 
nanopublication-based architectures when layered provenance is required.

The core class of OPINO is opino:Opinion, a subclass of dul:Description 
that represents a perspective-dependent description of an entity, 
premised on a construed state of affairs. The entity being described 
(via opino:describes) and the state of affairs that grounds the 
description (via opino:isPremisedOn) are distinct: the Opinion is a 
claim about an entity that results from the cognizer&apos;s construal of 
observable or documented facts. For instance, the opinion &apos;the Donation 
of Constantine is a forgery&apos; describes the Donation of Constantine, and 
is premised on a Construal involving the presence of anachronistic Latin, 
feudal terminology, and inconsistent dating formulae — facts perceived 
and interpreted by the cognizer as evidence for the claim. A different 
cognizer may construe the same facts differently, or construe different 
facts entirely, producing a different Opinion about the same entity.

An Opinion is not necessarily an interpretation in the hermeneutical 
sense. It may be as simple as &apos;Marco is good&apos; or &apos;this painting is 
beautiful&apos;. What distinguishes it from a neutral assertion of fact is 
its perspective-dependence: it is always the description of an entity 
as seen through the lens of a specific cognizer, grounded in what that 
cognizer perceives. The opino:Interpretation subclass is reserved for 
the specific case where an Opinion results from a deliberate 
hermeneutical interpretive act — formally represented as a 
hico:InterpretationAct in HiCO — involving a documented methodology, 
a set of criteria, and a source. An Interpretation inherits all the 
epistemic properties of Opinion while adding the full provenance layer 
provided by HiCO. Not every Opinion is an Interpretation: opinions 
formed in everyday discourse, automated extraction pipelines, or 
collective community processes may be generated by plain prov:Activity 
instances without the hermeneutical apparatus that HiCO models.

An Opinion is satisfied by a Construal — a perspective-dependent 
dul:Situation that reifies the set of facts as perceived by the 
cognizer, following the notion of construal from cognitive linguistics 
and social psychology (Ross 1987; Langacker 2008). The Construal is 
valid only when interpreted from the standpoint of a specific agent: 
the same objective state of affairs may be construed differently by 
different cognizers, leading to different Opinions over the same 
entities. The Opinion is the description that emerges from the analysis 
of a Construal — it is what the cognizer concludes from what they 
perceive, directed at the entity the claim is about.

Each Opinion carries an epistemic status, represented by an 
EpistemicStatusParameter valued by one of three EpistemicRegion 
individuals: AssertionValue (the holder commits to the claim as their 
current considered interpretation), HypothesisValue (the holder commits 
tentatively, pending further evidence), or ConjectureValue (the holder 
entertains the claim as a possibility without sufficient evidence to 
assert it). This determines whether an Opinion is classified as an 
opino:Assertion, opino:Hypothesis, or opino:Conjecture respectively, 
via owl:equivalentClass definitions.

Each Opinion is also tied to the provenance of its production via 
prov:wasGeneratedBy, which relates it to a prov:Activity. When the 
generating activity is a hico:InterpretationAct — as defined by the 
Historical Context Ontology (HiCO; Daquino and Tomasi 2015) — the 
Opinion is equivalent to an opino:Interpretation. HiCO provides the 
full provenance context of the interpretive act: the agent who performed 
it, the time, the methodology, and the source document. OPINO does not 
replicate this layer but bridges to it via the provenance relation.

Agreement, disagreement, and support between Opinions are deliberately 
kept outside the OPINO model. These dynamics are social and 
community-level epistemic phenomena, appropriately handled at the level 
of the prov:Activity node using CiTO properties (cito:agreesWith, 
cito:disagreesWith, cito:citesAsEvidence) as already provided by HiCO&apos;s 
integration with CiTO. OPINO focuses exclusively on the epistemic 
structure of the individual claim.

The properties of an Opinion are:
- opino:isPremisedOn — relates an Opinion to the Construal that 
  constitutes its premises (subproperty of dul:isSatisfiedBy)
- opino:hasEpistemicStatus — relates an Opinion to its 
  EpistemicStatusParameter (Functional; subproperty of dul:hasParameter)
- opino:heldBy — shortcut relating an Opinion directly to its holder 
  (range: owl:Thing; subproperty of dul:associatedWith)
- opino:describes — relates an Opinion to the entity its propositional 
  content is about (subproperty of dul:describes)
- opino:usesConcept — relates an Opinion to the concept being predicated 
  of its subject (subproperty of dul:usesConcept)
- prov:wasGeneratedBy — relates an Opinion to the prov:Activity that 
  produced it

Other properties of DUL can also be used to further describe the Opinion 
(such as dul:introduces). The core ones (opino:isPremisedOn, 
opino:describes, opino:usesConcept) were instantiated into OPINO for 
clarity, as subproperties of their DUL counterparts scoped to 
opino:Opinion as domain.

The properties of a Construal are:
- opino:grounds — relates a Construal to the Opinion it supports, as 
  premises support a conclusion (inverse of isPremisedOn; subproperty 
  of dul:satisfies)
- opino:involves — relates a Construal to any entity — object, agent, 
  event, or abstract concept — that the cognizer perceives as 
  participating in the construed state of affairs (subproperty of 
  dul:isSettingFor). When a Construal satisfies a Framester frame via 
  dul:satisfies, the roles of the involved entities can be made explicit 
  using Framester frame element properties (e.g. fe:Artifact.forgery, 
  fe:Means.forgery), providing a more granular representation without 
  requiring modification of the core pattern.
- opino:perceivedBy — relates a Construal to the cognizer whose 
  perspective constitutes it (range: owl:Thing; subproperty of 
  dul:associatedWith)
- opino:hasPart — relates a Construal to its constituent sub-Construals, 
  each representing an individual premise (subproperty of dul:hasPart; 
  allValuesFrom opino:Construal)
- opino:presupposes — relates a Construal to another Construal that must 
  hold as a logical or epistemic premise before it (subproperty of 
  dul:hasPrecondition)
- opino:enables — relates a Construal to another Construal it makes 
  possible as a subsequent inferential step (subproperty of 
  dul:hasPostcondition)
- dul:satisfies — optionally relates a sub-Construal to a dul:Description, 
  typically a Framester frame (Gangemi et al. 2016), providing the 
  conceptual vocabulary through which the construed state of affairs 
  is interpreted

A Construal can be extended in two ways. First, by converting it into 
a TimeIndexedConstrual — a subclass of opino:Construal equivalent to a 
Construal that has at least one opino:holdsAtTime relation pointing to a 
dul:TimeInterval — for temporally bounded perceptions, such as &apos;yesterday 
Marco did something good&apos; or &apos;this painting was attributed to Caravaggio 
during the period 1990–2005&apos;. Second, by decomposing it into 
sub-Construals via opino:hasPart, each of which may itself be satisfied 
by a Framester frame describing the inferential role of that premise 
within the overall construal. Sub-Construals can be ordered via 
opino:presupposes and opino:enables to represent the logical sequence 
of the inferential chain.

OPINO is informed by the CRMinf extension of CIDOC CRM, the Digital 
Hermeneutics model (Daquino, Pasqual and Tomasi 2021), and the SEBI 
ontology (https://valentinapasqual.github.io/sebi/). It is released 
under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License 
(CC BY 4.0)</dc:description>
        <dc:description xml:lang="en">OPINO is a content Ontology Design Pattern for representing scholarly interpretive opinions. It extends the Description and Situation (DnS) ODP by introducing epistemic status gradation, inter-opinion relations, and a provenance layer via PROV-O and HiCO. It is informed by the Digital Hermeneutics model (Daquino et al., 2021) and the SEBI ontology (https://valentinapasqual.github.io/sebi/).</dc:description>
        <dc:title xml:lang="en">OPINO - OPINion ONtology</dc:title>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">OPINO - OPINion ONtology</rdfs:label>
        <owl:versionInfo>0.1.0</owl:versionInfo>
    </owl:Ontology>
    


    <!-- 
    ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
    //
    // Annotation properties
    //
    ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
     -->


    


    <!-- http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/creator -->


    <owl:AnnotationProperty rdf:about="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/creator"/>
    


    <!-- http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date -->


    <owl:AnnotationProperty rdf:about="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date"/>
    


    <!-- http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/description -->


    <owl:AnnotationProperty rdf:about="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/description"/>
    


    <!-- http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title -->


    <owl:AnnotationProperty rdf:about="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title"/>
    


    <!-- http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#qualifiedCardinality -->


    <owl:AnnotationProperty rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#qualifiedCardinality"/>
    


    <!-- 
    ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
    //
    // Object Properties
    //
    ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
     -->


    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/describes -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/describes">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#describes"/>
        <owl:inverseOf rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/isDescribedBy"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#Entity"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Relates an Opinion to the entity its propositional content is about — the subject of the claim.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">describes</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/enables -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/enables">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#hasPostcondition"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Construal"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Construal"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Relates a Construal to another Construal that it makes possible as a subsequent step in an inferential chain. A Construal enables another when it provides the evidential or logical basis from which the subsequent Construal can be constituted. For example, the Construal &apos;Fief is a Medieval Latin term&apos; enables the Construal &apos;The Donation contains anachronistic Latin&apos;, which in turn grounds the Opinion &apos;The Donation is a Forgery&apos;. Inverse counterpart of opino:presupposes in the inferential chain, though not declared as a formal OWL inverse. Subproperty of dul:hasPostcondition.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">enables</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/grounds -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/grounds">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#satisfies"/>
        <owl:inverseOf rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/isPremisedOn"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Construal"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Relates a Construal to the Opinion it supports as premises support a conclusion. Inverse of opino:isPremisedOn. Subproperty of dul:satisfies, preserving full DnS semantics.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">grounds</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicRegion -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicRegion">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#hasRegion"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/EpistemicStatusParameter"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/EpistemicRegion"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Relates an EpistemicStatusParameter to the EpistemicRegion individual that represents its value in the epistemic quality space. Functional because each EpistemicStatusParameter is valued by exactly one EpistemicRegion at any given time. Subproperty of dul:hasRegion, scoped to opino:EpistemicStatusParameter as domain and opino:EpistemicRegion as range.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has epistemic region</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicStatus -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/hasEpistemicStatus">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#hasParameter"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/EpistemicStatusParameter"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Relates an Opinion to the parameter that carries its current epistemic status value. Functional because each Opinion has exactly one epistemic status at any given time.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has epistemic status</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/hasPart -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/hasPart">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#hasPart"/>
        <owl:inverseOf rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/isPartOf"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Construal"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#Situation"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Relates a Construal to its constituent sub-situations, each representing an individual premise as perceived by the cognizer. The relation is recursive — a sub-Situation may itself have parts that ground it further, mirroring the CRMinf premise chain (J1 usedAsPremise). Each sub-Situation may optionally satisfy a dul:Description (e.g. a Framester frame), representing the inference logic (CRMinf J3 applies) through which that premise is interpreted. The conclusion drawn from the full Construal is always an opino:Opinion (dul:Description), connected via opino:grounds.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has part</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/heldBy -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/heldBy">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#associatedWith"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Shortcut property relating an opino:Opinion directly to the agent who holds it. Equivalent to navigating opino:Opinion --prov:wasGeneratedBy--&gt; prov:Activity --prov:wasAssociatedWith--&gt; prov:Agent. Retained for querying convenience.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">held by</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/holdsAtTime -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/holdsAtTime">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#includesTime"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Construal"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#TimeInterval"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Relates a TimeIndexedConstrual to the TimeInterval during which the construed state of affairs holds. A TimeIndexedConstrual represents a perspective-dependent set of facts that are valid only within a specific temporal bound — this property makes that bound explicit. For example, the attribution of a painting to the School of Caravaggio as perceived by the Zeri Foundation holds during the interval 1990–2005.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">holds at time</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/involves -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/involves">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#isSettingFor"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Construal"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#Entity"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Relates a Construal to any entity — object, agent, event, or abstract concept — that the cognizer perceives as participating in the construed state of affairs. Following the social psychology notion of construal (Ross 1987), the entities involved are not neutral facts but are perceived and interpreted through the cognizer&apos;s subjective lens. The Construal grounds the Opinion (subclass of Description).</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">involves</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/isDescribedBy -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/isDescribedBy">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#isDescribedBy"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#Entity"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Inverse of opino:describes.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">is described by</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/isPartOf -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/isPartOf">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#isPartOf"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Construal"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Construal"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Inverse of opino:hasPart</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">is part of</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/isPremisedOn -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/isPremisedOn">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#isSatisfiedBy"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Construal"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Relates an Opinion to the Construal that constitutes its premises — the set of facts as perceived by the cognizer from which the Opinion results as a conclusion. Subproperty of dul:isSatisfiedBy, preserving full DnS semantics.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">is premised on</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/perceivedBy -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/perceivedBy">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#associatedWith"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Construal"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Relates a Construal to the cognizer whose perspective constitutes it. Shortcut for: grounds inverse → Opinion → prov:wasGeneratedBy → Activity → prov:wasAssociatedWith → Agent.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">perceived by</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/presupposes -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/presupposes">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#hasPrecondition"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Construal"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Construal"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Relates a Construal to another Construal  that must hold as a logical premise before it. Represents the inferential ordering between premise Construals in a chain of reasoning — the &apos;presupposed&apos; Construal provides the evidential or logical ground that the dependent Construal builds upon. For example, the Construal &apos;Fief is a Medieval Latin term&apos; is the presupposition of the Construal &apos;The Donation contains anachronistic Latin&apos;. Subproperty of dul:hasPrecondition, defined in DUL as direct precedence applied to situations.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">presupposes</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://w3id.org/opino/usesConcept -->


    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://w3id.org/opino/usesConcept">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#usesConcept"/>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://w3id.org/opino/Opinion"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#Concept"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Relates an Opinion to the concept being predicated of its subject. </rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">http://w3id.org/opino/</rdfs:isDefinedBy>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">uses concept</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


